r the Centre was 69% of the total budget. A more detailed breakdown of budget versus expenditure is shown in Annex 4.3. EU; 569,743; 2% UNDP TRAC; 7,999,051; 2 7% AusAID; 6,977,828; 24% NZAID; 3,563,689; 12% AusAID Other; 4,993,855; 17% British High Comm; 42,637; 0% Japan; 150,000; 1% UN Other; 4,859,734; 17% Resource Mobilization 2008-2011 MDG\u2019s; 897,459; 17% GovPac; 869,371; 16% CPR; 2,250,423; 43% PFIP; 720,466; 14% RCSP; 539,809; 10% UNDP Pacific Centre Expenditure Delivery as at 31 December 2010 UNDP PACIFIC CENTRE ANNUAL REPORT 2010 29 The Asia Pacific Regional Programme for 2008-2011, under which the Pacific Centre operates, has been extended to 2013 to be in line with UNDP\u2019s global Strategic Plan. As a result, instead of 2011 being the penultimate year for the programme we now have a three year horizon for our work. Over the next three years, the Centre will continue to work under all four pillars of MDG Achievement and Poverty reduction that also cover environment and energy and HIV and AIDS; Financial Inclusion, Democratic Governance; and Crisis Prevention and Recovery. However, in doing so it will seek to respond to actions that bring results; on emerging issues where UNDP is considered to have a comparative advantage; and where there is considered to be potential for multidimensional impact. A major aim going forward will be for the Centre to work with UNDP colleagues to strengthen the integration of global, regional and country support available from UNDP and other UN agencies.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "6f7cbf19-a9b4-42ef-b588-f0bd50672016": {"__data__": {"id_": "6f7cbf19-a9b4-42ef-b588-f0bd50672016", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/pacific-centre-annual-report-2010", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher":