ster risk reduction by working with a wide range of partners to share knowledge and experience and the promotion of integrated approaches to mitigation, adaptation and livelihood initiatives \u2022 Continue to support measures to promote peace and security, good governance and sustainable human development through more effective democratic institutions that ensure human rights and enhanced service delivery for all in the community \u2022 Boost the results and policy impact of gender equality and women\u2019s empowerment initiatives \u2022 Strengthen opportunities for increased south-south cooperation, knowledge sharing and communications The Way Forward UNDP PACIFIC CENTRE ANNUAL REPORT 2010 30 Garry Wiseman Manager Democratic Governance Team Ernesto Bautista Pacific Regional Governance Advisor and Project Manager Nurina Widgado Governance Programme Specialist Charmaine Rodrigues Governance Institution & Accountabilty Specialist Masanobu Yasukawa UNV-Communications & Support Officer Isikeli Valemei Governance Programme Associate Millennium Development Goals Team Ahmed Moustafa Pacific Regional Macre Economic & Poverty Reduction Advisor and Project Manager Carol Flore-Smereczniak Pacific Regional MDG Specialist Thomas Jensen Environment and Energy Specialist Ferdinand Strobel HIV & AIDS Programme Specialist Mahezabeen Khan MDG Programme Associate Pacific Financial Inclusion Team Tillman Bruett Pacific Financial Inclusion Advisor Jeff Liew Regional Partnership & Business Development Manager Joep", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "e3ab819a-1217-4d1f-b1a3-441f3a682f60": {"__data__": {"id_": "e3ab819a-1217-4d1f-b1a3-441f3a682f60", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/pacific-centre-annual-report-2010", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "Unite