otest movement that had included the burning of company equipment and confrontations with armed police (see Horowitz 2012). However, I argue that although this IBA eliminated the physical violence associated with the mining project, it furthered both ecolo Corporate environmental violence may involve direct harm to ecosystems but, like social violence, it is often indirect. Another form of indirect violence is cultural violence, belief systems that can be used to embodies often masks coercion by concealing the negotiation process, its social context, and the res In Kanak (New Caledonian Melanesian) societies, women are expected to defer to men, who hold all customary positions of power.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "16fcf894-d7b1-4981-a91f-65dcfa06e817": {"__data__": {"id_": "16fcf894-d7b1-4981-a91f-65dcfa06e817", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/advancing-sustainable-development-case-extractive-industries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Advancing Sustainable Development: The Case of Extractive Industries", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/advancing-sustainable-development-case-extractive-industries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "791e723c68f8afcbb2d9b3a87db990381914c96af2789192377598e3ce20d94c"}, "2": {"node_id": "d595b15d-e8f8-4b35-929a-99396e08dc37", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/advancing-sustainable-development-case-extractive-industries"